SQL Database Administrator/Windows Systems Support
Location: Phoenix, AZ ( LOCALS ONLY )
1 year
JOB QUALIFICATIONS: 
Requires experience in programming, developing, and maintaining vendor and custom  databases.  
Must have skills in database design and support utilizing relational or on-line transaction based databases. 
Must have knowledge of HP UNIX, SQL, Cache, and Crystal Reports programs.  
Must have good math and reasoning skills.  
Experience:  Requires at least three to four (3-4) years experience in Database design/development, programming and support utilizing relational or on-line transaction based databases
 
Education or equivalency:  Requires a Bachelors degree in Computer Science or related field; or an equivalent  combination of training and progressively responsible experience that will result in the  required specialized knowledge and abilities to perform the assigned work..
Preferred to have:
Would like to have three to five (3-5) years experience in an enterprise data center environment with above knowledge, skills and abilities. Support experience should include in-depth knowledge of most, if not all, of the following:  MS ACTIVE DIRECTORY, MS SQL, MS EXCHANGE, VISIO, DHCP, WINS, DNS, VMWARE 3/ESX, VB SCRIPT, POWERSHELL, WMI, WSUS, AV, CITRIX, NAS/SAN, LINUX, BLACKBERRY (BES) and BACKUP software and TAPE LIBRARY technologies
 
MARGINAL/ADDITIONAL FUNCTIONS: 
 1. Work with users and departments to review current data base applications and technology.  Recommend alternative data base and application functionality to improve application functionality and data reliability. 
2. Assists with other department functions as assigned. 
 
If you have any questions please feel free to call me.
 
Thanks & Regards,
Arun Chandupatla.
Hallmark Global Technologies Inc. 
262 Chapman Rd, Suite # 101, 
Newark, DE- 19702.
Direct:  302-525-4225
Alt : 302-355-2324/302-525-4228/
Mailto:  carun@hgtechinc.net 
Fax: 302-366-8961
www.hgtechinc.net
